143
00:06:56,374 --> 00:06:58,376
I wish there was something I could do.

144
00:06:58,459 --> 00:07:01,379
Uh, yeah, that definitely falls
under the category of...

145
00:07:01,462 --> 00:07:03,172
Not my sink, not my dishes?

146
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:05,216
I was gonna say,
not your garden, not your weeds,

147
00:07:05,299 --> 00:07:06,676
but same thing.

148
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:07,759
I know.

149
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:10,388
Maybe I should reach out to him.

150
00:07:10,471 --> 00:07:15,268
Do you not remember how hard it was
seeing him and his wife at Majid's party?

151
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:18,813
I really think
I have to put all that stuff to the side.

152
00:07:18,896 --> 00:07:22,775
That business is cutthroat.
People can turn on you in a second.

153
00:07:22,859 --> 00:07:27,363
You know, he probably
needs a friend right now.

154
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:29,073
You're gonna be his friend?

155
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:30,450
He'd do it for me.

156
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:34,120
And he would do it for you too, Sash.
You know that.

157
00:07:34,203 --> 00:07:35,413
Okay, fine.

158
00:07:37,206 --> 00:07:39,542
Are you sure you
aren't wanting to reach out to Brad

159
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,461
'cause you're in a bad place with Majid?

160
00:07:42,170 --> 00:07:43,838
We're not in a bad place.

161
00:07:44,755 --> 00:07:46,090
We're in no place.

162
00:07:46,174 --> 00:07:49,302
He hasn't reached out since the party
and neither have I.

163
00:07:49,385 --> 00:07:51,387
I haven't even had time to think about it.

164
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:54,307
- This is my first day back in the city.
- I know.

165
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:56,517
It's gonna be what it's gonna be.

166
00:07:56,601 --> 00:08:01,481
But me reaching out to Brad
has nothing to do with Majid.

167
00:08:03,065 --> 00:08:04,609
I'm gonna text him.

168
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:11,990
Hey.

169
00:08:12,575 --> 00:08:13,618
Hey.

170
00:08:13,701 --> 00:08:15,620
Do you want me
to cancel my shoot and stay?

171
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:19,373
I'm happy to.
I want to support you in any way I can.

172
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:21,834
It'll all be fine. I'm gonna beat this.

173
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:23,044
Of course you are.

174
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:26,714
You're Brad Simon,
you always come out on top.

175
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:28,757
[cell phone chimes]

176
00:08:33,971 --> 00:08:34,971
What is it?

177
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:39,894
It's nothing. Just...

178
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:42,563
It's just one of the lawyers.

179
00:08:46,651 --> 00:08:47,651
Listen...

180
00:08:49,153 --> 00:08:51,656
I'm not just here
for the good times, okay?

181
00:08:52,281 --> 00:08:54,951
I want you to know
you can lean on me all the time.

182
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:56,661
I'm your wife.

183
00:09:03,876 --> 00:09:05,086
Don't forget to eat.

184
00:09:08,381 --> 00:09:09,381
I won't.

185
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:11,634
You have a good shoot, okay?

186
00:09:33,990 --> 00:09:34,824
Nothing.

187
00:09:34,907 --> 00:09:37,159
A least someone has good boundaries.

188
00:09:39,495 --> 00:09:41,747
Oh, wait. He's writing back.

189
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,126
