190
00:09:45,209 --> 00:09:46,460
Oh, for fuck's sake.

191
00:09:46,544 --> 00:09:47,920
I have to be there for him.

192
00:09:48,004 --> 00:09:49,839
It's the right thing to do.

193
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:06,605
His loft.

194
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:09,149
You know what?

195
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:12,820
I have enough of a clusterfuck of my own
to deal with today.

196
00:10:12,903 --> 00:10:15,406
Have fun being Brad's friend.

197
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:18,034
I'm sure that's gonna be
super easy for you.

198
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:40,473
[Brad] Thanks for coming.

199
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:45,269
- For reaching out.
- Of course. Yeah.

200
00:10:46,354 --> 00:10:48,856
Where's, um, Gigi?

201
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:50,690
She's...

202
00:10:51,859 --> 00:10:53,235
She's on a shoot.

203
00:10:55,237 --> 00:10:56,572
Do you want a coffee?

204
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:57,490
- Sure.
- Yeah.

205
00:10:57,573 --> 00:10:58,616
Yeah.

206
00:11:10,044 --> 00:11:11,170
[moaning]

207
00:11:25,601 --> 00:11:26,936
You have a new couch.

208
00:11:28,229 --> 00:11:29,355
It's pink.

209
00:11:30,147 --> 00:11:31,399
It's blush.

210
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:33,859
I was assured of that.

211
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:37,571
And you're a Buddhist now.

212
00:11:38,948 --> 00:11:40,324
Uh, Gigi got it.

213
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:42,451
She's made a few changes here.

214
00:11:43,994 --> 00:11:45,121
[Billie] I can see that.

215
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:51,334
Thank you.

216
00:11:54,463 --> 00:11:55,339
You wanna sit?

217
00:11:55,423 --> 00:11:57,133
- Yeah.
- Yeah, yeah.

218
00:12:08,018 --> 00:12:11,105
You were the first person I wanted to call
when it all happened.

219
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:15,443
You always warned me about Ron.

220
00:12:17,528 --> 00:12:19,238
I really fucked up. I...

221
00:12:21,073 --> 00:12:23,701
I wasn't overseeing the day-to-day
the way I should have.

222
00:12:24,577 --> 00:12:26,120
I knew Ron was tough...

223
00:12:27,913 --> 00:12:30,291
but I had no idea he was stealing.
I swear.

224
00:12:30,374 --> 00:12:31,876
Of course you didn't.

225
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:34,753
I should've listened to you.

226
00:12:38,048 --> 00:12:40,176
You've always known what's good for me.

227
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:42,761
Before I know it myself.

228
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:47,266
I'm always coming around too late.

229
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:53,439
I think I'm gonna lose the company.

230
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,569
I don't know who I am without it.

231
00:12:59,778 --> 00:13:00,778
Brad...

232
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:04,241
You are not your company.

233
00:13:05,326 --> 00:13:09,163
I know how much it means to you
and meant to you for your dad.

234
00:13:09,246 --> 00:13:11,999
But you made all that right
before he passed.

235
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:14,793
There is so much more to you
than your success.

236
00:13:15,794 --> 00:13:18,088
I'm about to be a father, Billie.

237
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:22,092
And I'm scared to death.

238
00:13:24,136 --> 00:13:25,136
The money...

239
00:13:25,971 --> 00:13:29,225
was the one thing
I knew I had going for me.

240
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,310
You know?

241
00:13:32,353 --> 00:13:34,146
I knew, if nothing else, I...

242
00:13:38,859 --> 00:13:40,486
I could provide for my son.

243
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:43,196
But now...

244
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:48,577
You're gonna be a great father.

245
00:13:50,704 --> 00:13:52,456
I've always known that.

246
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:57,169
Whether it happened with us or with Gigi.

247
00:14:01,131 --> 00:14:02,800
That little boy is lucky...

248
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:05,052
to have you as his dad.

249
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:50,306
You don't want to do this.

250
00:14:53,934 --> 00:14:54,934
Maybe I do.

251
00:15:01,483 --> 00:15:02,483
Well, I don't.

252
00:15:08,949 --> 00:15:09,949
I can't.

253
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:15,915
You've always been right about me too.

254
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:21,337
This isn't who I am, who I want to be.

255
00:15:23,088 --> 00:15:24,632
This is not who you are either.

256
00:15:37,895 --> 00:15:40,272
[new age music playing over speakers]

257
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:41,482
